Use mermaid `mindmap` syntax. Indentation (two spaces per level) defines the
hierarchy. The first line must be `mindmap`, followed by a single root node. Example:

mindmap
  root((Central Topic))
    Subtopic A
      Detail 1
      Detail 2
    Subtopic B
      Detail 3

Rules:
- Exactly one root node, wrapped as `root((Central Topic))`.
- Maximum depth: {{ max_depth }} levels (including the root).
- Each node label is concise (ideally 2–5 words); derive everything from the content.
- Keep labels plain text; avoid characters that break mermaid (no unescaped `(`, `)`, `:`, `#`, `;` inside labels).
- Group related ideas under shared parents; aim for a balanced, readable tree.

